# 2. イメージ

Kanade: (I'm glad that Dad was doing okay.)
Kanade: (We actually got to talk a little today... So, once I get home, I'll keep working on that song.)
Kanade: (But...)
Kanade: In that case... I'll try composing a song based on that memory next.
Kanade: A warm memory...
???: <Kanade.>
Kanade: Huh...?
Kanade: Rin? What brings you here?
Rin: <I was bored, so I decided to see how you were doing. Remember how you talked about composing that song for Mafuyu?>
Kanade: Right. I'm going to start on that song once I get home.
Rin: <Oh?>
Rin: <Did something happen, Kanade?>
Kanade: Huh?
Rin: <You seemed a little worried just now.>
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: You're right.
Kanade: The song isn't really coming together well.
Kanade: I just can't get a clear vision of it...
Rin: <A clear vision...?>
Kanade: Um... I have a better understanding of what the warmth Mafuyu has been feeling involves.
Kanade: But I just can't tie that together with her mother.
Kanade: Because she feels like the complete opposite of that to me.
Rin: <The complete opposite?>
Kanade: Yes. When I actually met her...
Kanade: She felt so cold.
Rin: <Cold...>
Kanade: Yes... I can't really put it into words, but she felt like an icy shiver down my spine.
Kanade: Also, during our conversation, I got the distinct feeling that she wasn't really thinking of what was best for Mafuyu at all.
Kanade: So... I just can't picture that person as the source of the “warmth” Mafuyu feels.
Kanade: That's likely why I'm struggling right now.
Rin: <This is hard...>
Kanade: It is. I don't know what to do...
Rin: <...>
Rin: <I don't really understand these things...>
Rin: <But if Mafuyu feels that “warmth” from her mother in her memories...>
Rin: <Then it must exist inside her somewhere, right?>
Kanade: Good point...
Kanade: (She's right. I don't actually know that much about Mafuyu's mom. But...)
Kanade: (That frigid gaze...)
???: Ms. Yoisaki?
Kanade: Huh? Oh...
Mafuyu's Father: Hello. What a coincidence to see you here.
Kanade: Um, yes, it really is. Are you doing some shopping, Mr. Asahina?
Mafuyu's Father: Yes, I'm buying things for dinner. We're having hot pot tonight.
Kanade: Hot pot... That sounds like a nice way to stay warm.
Kanade: Maybe Mafuyu and I can also have that tonight...
Mafuyu's Father: Yes, please do.
Mafuyu's Father: How has Mafuyu been lately?
Kanade: Huh?
Mafuyu's Father: Ah, forgive me. I want to believe that I have a good idea of how she's doing, since I've been seeing and talking to her each week...
Mafuyu's Father: But I imagine she still doesn't feel comfortable telling me certain things.
Mafuyu's Father: I just hope she isn't pushing herself too hard...
Kanade: Oh...
Mafuyu's Father: Ah, of course, you don't have to tell me if you don't feel comfortable. But any information would be greatly appreciated...
Kanade: Mafuyu seems much more at ease compared to before.
Kanade: Before, she was always withdrawn, and constantly worried about her family...
Kanade: But she's seemed much more stable lately.
Kanade: And I believe you've played a big role in that, Mr. Asahina, since you've made a genuine effort to understand what's been going on with her.
Mafuyu's Father: ...
Mafuyu's Father: I see...
Kanade: I really have to compose that song...
Mafuyu's Father: Compose?
Kanade: Oh, I'm sorry...
Kanade: So, I'm trying to compose a song for Mafuyu right now.
Mafuyu's Father: A song? For Mafuyu?
Kanade: Yes.
Kanade: She's actually smiled several times after listening to my songs.
Kanade: I know a single song won't be enough to turn this current situation around...
Kanade: But if I can write a song that will lessen Mafuyu's burdens, even a little...
Kanade: Then I want to.
Mafuyu's Father: I had no idea...
Mafuyu's Father: Thank you very much. You really have done so much for her.
Mafuyu's Father: I wish I could repay your generosity somehow...
Kanade: No, I don't need...
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: Actually, if possible...
Kanade: Could you tell me more about Mafuyu's mother?
